text.section:
Revenues of a cooperative for a fiscal year may be used:
To pay the expenses of operating and maintaining the facilities of the cooperative during the fiscal year;
To pay interest and principal obligations of the cooperative that are due in the fiscal year;
To the extent determined by the board of directors, to finance or provide a reserve for the financing of the construction or acquisition by the cooperative of additional facilities;
To provide a reasonable reserve for working capital;
To provide a reserve for the payment of the indebtedness of the cooperative in an amount not less than the total interest and principal payments that are due during the next fiscal year;
To provide for education about cooperatives; and
To provide for the dissemination of information about the effective use of electricity and services made available by the cooperative.
